486
00:44:43,319 --> 00:44:47,269
<i>He walked me home</i> and he
sang that song he always sings.

487
00:44:47,897 --> 00:44:49,582
<i>I saw him, too, last night.

488
00:44:50,582 --> 00:44:54,259
<i>Plain as day.</i>
It was a dream, Honey

489
00:44:59,766 --> 00:45:01,331
I saw him.

490
00:45:04,035 --> 00:45:06,045
None of you believe me.

491
00:45:07,758 --> 00:45:10,628
Baby, now, listen,
Gaten has gone on to heaven.

492
00:45:11,593 --> 00:45:12,962
I'm going to bed.

493
00:45:25,066 --> 00:45:27,561
- Thanks for all your help.
- Well, I know what it's like.

494
00:45:27,611 --> 00:45:30,603
I'm raisin' a daughter
since my wife passed on.

495
00:45:31,161 --> 00:45:33,961
So, if you ever need any
help, don't hesitate to call.

496
00:45:34,364 --> 00:45:37,107
That's very nice, Mister...?

497
00:45:37,387 --> 00:45:38,492
Chase.

498
00:45:38,542 --> 00:45:40,461
Chase Porter,
I was a friend to Gaten.

499
00:45:43,220 --> 00:45:44,677
Well, I better get goin'.

500
00:45:47,072 --> 00:45:50,077
What can I say about
the most obvious thing?

501
00:45:50,427 --> 00:45:53,825
And I would say the same thing to a
black parent raising a white child...

502
00:45:54,742 --> 00:45:56,159
It never works.

503
00:45:57,186 --> 00:46:01,363
Look, it's not going to be easy
for her to come back to school.

504
