In some ways, this building was more
home to Gaten and Clover than home was.

505
00:46:07,473 --> 00:46:11,145
He made this school,
his memory is everywhere.

506
00:46:11,677 --> 00:46:13,000
Any suggestions?

507
00:46:14,886 --> 00:46:19,809
A great deal of love,
and a very firm hand.

508
00:46:21,614 --> 00:46:26,732
One thing you can tell Clover: she'll be
in the gifted and talented class this year.

509
00:46:28,142 --> 00:46:30,343
I'm sure she'll
be very pleased.

510
00:46:30,593 --> 00:46:32,791
I can't be in the gifted
and talented class.

511
00:46:32,841 --> 00:46:34,218
Why not?

512
00:46:34,268 --> 00:46:35,767
You've been with
me all summer,

513
00:46:35,817 --> 00:46:39,087
have you seen one sign that
I'm even gifted or talented?

514
00:46:39,137 --> 00:46:43,313
Uh... well... it will all seem better
when you get some new clothes for school.

515
00:46:43,363 --> 00:46:45,071
I don't want new clothes!

516
00:46:45,529 --> 00:46:47,503
I... I don't want new anything!

517
00:46:47,553 --> 00:46:49,762
I just want things to
be the way they were!

518
00:46:54,946 --> 00:46:56,171
What is this?

519
00:46:57,140 --> 00:46:58,606
Pot salad.

520
00:46:59,506 --> 00:47:03,284
It's a balanced, nutritional meal...
proteins, carbohydrates...

521
00:47:03,334 --> 00:47:05,426
I don't want a
science project!

522
00:47:05,476 --> 00:47:07,562
- I just want some lunch!
- What's going on?

523
00:47:07,612 --> 00:47:10,891
- I've never seen you like this.
- I'm gonna eat at the peach shed.

524
00:47:10,941 --> 00:47:13,060
Sit down and eat your lunch!

525
00:47:13,733 --> 00:47:15,855
Take your practice
salad and shove it!

526
00:47:15,905 --> 00:47:17,893
Damn it!
Clover!

527
00:47:18,620 --> 00:47:19,660
Get back here!

528
00:47:20,505 --> 00:47:22,333
- That any way to talk to Sara Kate?
- Shut up!

529
00:47:22,383 --> 00:47:25,125
- How dare you talk to me that way.
- I wasn't talking to you.

530
00:47:25,175 --> 00:47:26,851
Clover, you're going to get back
in there and you're going to eat your...

531
00:47:26,901 --> 00:47:30,343
Everleen needs me, and you
don't want to cross Everleen.

532
00:47:30,393 --> 00:47:33,877
She'll throw the bones at you<i> and
then you'll be sorry,</i> you'll see!

533
00:47:34,958 --> 00:47:36,101
Throw the bones?

534
00:47:39,184 --> 00:47:41,340
Clover, you are not going
out in those clothes.

535
00:47:41,390 --> 00:47:44,432
Clover, you're gonna get back in there and
you're gonna eat your lunch, then Clover...

536
00:47:44,482 --> 00:47:45,746
Clover you're going to clean your room.

537
00:47:45,796 --> 00:47:48,042
Clover!
Clover!

538
00:47:48,092 --> 00:47:49,818
Stay out of my road!

539
00:47:50,704 --> 00:47:51,800
Clover!

540
00:47:53,835 --> 00:47:55,686
So much for the firm idea.

541
00:47:57,226 --> 00:48:03,789
Psychiatrists! Good heavens!
I see those talk shows.

542
00:48:04,570 --> 00:48:07,988
- Terrible people.
- She has to talk to someone.

543
00:48:08,038 --> 00:48:12,818
You! She needs to talk with you!
You're her mother now.

544
00:48:12,968 --> 00:48:15,604
She started,
but I think I frightened her.

545
00:48:16,348 --> 00:48:18,404
Of course she's frightened,

546
00:48:19,433 --> 00:48:21,755
poor child's livin'
with a white woman,

547
00:48:22,005 --> 00:48:24,531
that's enough to frighten anybody.

548
00:48:25,205 --> 00:48:27,383
Are white women
really so terrible?

549
00:48:29,531 --> 00:48:30,770
White women?

550
00:48:30,820 --> 00:48:34,618
Terrible people! Cold, distant,

551
00:48:35,023 --> 00:48:40,025
work your fingers to the bone for the
last few dollars they begrudge you.

552
00:48:40,399 --> 00:48:43,544
I see your point...
my mother is a white woman.

553
00:48:45,646 --> 00:48:48,108
Clover says she SEES Gaten.

554
00:48:50,081 --> 00:48:52,933
Really?
How is he doin'?

555
00:48:53,451 --> 00:48:57,752
- This doesn't bother you?
- Be bother me more if she didn't.

556
00:48:58,423 --> 00:49:02,789
Somebody has to look after the dead...
ease 'em through "The Passage".

557
00:49:03,194 --> 00:49:08,909
It should be in a dump, but the
Hills are not a grieving family.

558
00:49:09,401 --> 00:49:14,946
They turn their sorrow into work and
the Lord blesses them for their labor.

559
00:49:15,978 --> 00:49:18,849
But it leaves the
child alone to grieve.

560
00:49:20,057 --> 00:49:22,473
I almost think I saw
him the other night.

561
00:49:23,647 --> 00:49:26,182
You did?
How'd ya feel?

562
00:49:26,232 --> 00:49:28,391
Thrilled.

563
00:49:29,578 --> 00:49:35,147
For a second, then it was like...
losing him all over again.

564
00:49:35,197 --> 00:49:39,084
How do you think the child feels?
The child is grievin'.

565
00:49:39,134 --> 00:49:43,063
Hard work,
there's nobody willin' to do it.

566
00:49:43,113 --> 00:49:46,731
- She needs company.
- Even from a white woman?

567
00:49:46,781 --> 00:49:47,881
Has nothin' to do with race.

568
00:49:47,931 --> 00:49:49,389
<i>Thank God for that.

569
00:49:49,439 --> 00:49:52,826
Oh, this is harder that
race, this is family.

570
00:49:52,876 --> 00:49:55,613
There is nothin'
harder than family.

571
00:49:55,872 --> 00:49:58,336
You are a wise, old woman.

572
00:49:59,482 --> 00:50:01,869
Age has nothin'
to do with it.

573
00:50:03,073 --> 00:50:05,801
I was smart when
I was young.

574
00:50:07,530 --> 00:50:10,926
Go on, finish up your lemonade,
you're keepin' me from my soups.

575
00:51:05,142 --> 00:51:09,773
Clover, when you see Gaten,
how do you see him?

576
00:51:12,902 --> 00:51:15,565
First I feel him...
behind me.

577
00:51:16,106 --> 00:51:18,077
When I turn,
sometimes he's there...

578
00:51:18,645 --> 00:51:20,318
sometimes not.

579
00:51:20,939 --> 00:51:23,035
If he's not there I get sad.

580
00:51:23,719 --> 00:51:25,510
I was sad once.

581
00:51:27,439 --> 00:51:29,966
So sad I didn't feel
like living anymore.

582
00:51:30,381 --> 00:51:31,603
Why?

583
00:51:33,563 --> 00:51:37,592
Well...
found out I couldn't have children.

584
00:51:40,912 --> 00:51:43,562
I wanted to die,
I was very sad.

585
00:51:44,546 --> 00:51:46,644
You wanted a kid that bad?

586
00:51:49,845 --> 00:51:51,355
Still do.

587
00:51:57,350 --> 00:52:00,175
You don't want to ruin my
drawing, you better not smile.

588
00:52:19,326 --> 00:52:20,839
What the hell.

589
00:52:31,852 --> 00:52:34,622
<i>Oh, I hope I'm not disturbin'.

590
00:52:34,672 --> 00:52:36,233
Not at all,
not at all.

591
00:52:38,415 --> 00:52:40,749
Some of the back of your house
is gettin' out of control and

592
00:52:40,799 --> 00:52:45,397
I had some time this mornin',
so, I brought my ridin' mower.

593
00:52:45,447 --> 00:52:47,058
Wasn't that thoughtful.

594
00:52:48,457 --> 00:52:50,351
C'mon in, have a seat.

595
00:52:54,757 --> 00:52:57,580
Clover! We've got company.

596
00:53:03,756 --> 00:53:06,609
Ya know, I used to come
here when Gaten was...

597
00:53:06,659 --> 00:53:08,674
<i>Well, Gaten was a friend.

598
00:53:08,924 --> 00:53:11,104
Once, you came here once.

599
00:53:11,154 --> 00:53:13,459
And you weren't really
that good a friend.

600
00:53:13,588 --> 00:53:16,462
<i>- How's your daughter, Chase?</i>
- She's a pig.

601
00:53:16,512 --> 00:53:19,188
Claire's at an awkward age.

602
00:53:19,238 --> 00:53:22,668
But she's fine, just fine,
she has a birthday comin' up.

603
00:53:22,718 --> 00:53:25,663
<i>- You and Clover are invited.
- Oh, great.

604
00:53:32,594 --> 00:53:34,909
Seems like everybody's
in church but us.

605
00:53:40,054 --> 00:53:43,473
- Clover, maybe she's...
- Well, I better get to work.

606
00:53:43,523 --> 00:53:46,523
- Have some iced tea first.
- Oh, I'll get it, Chase, how do you like it?

607
00:53:46,573 --> 00:53:48,307
Well, no sugar, please.

608
00:54:31,094 --> 00:54:32,886
My! That's good iced tea.

609
00:54:33,600 --> 00:54:37,143
- Just the way I like it.
- That's what I thought.

610
00:54:57,713 --> 00:55:00,689
Hey, Stranger,
<i>I'm lookin' for my little girl.

611
00:55:00,974 --> 00:55:03,252
It's not going to work this time, Gaten.

612
00:55:03,302 --> 00:55:06,706
You won't talk to anybody else,
so everybody thinks I'm crazy.

613
00:55:06,756 --> 00:55:09,858
Sweetheart, I talk,
they... they just don't listen.

614
00:55:09,908 --> 00:55:12,581
Well, then I'm not going
to listen anymore either.

615
00:55:13,646 --> 00:55:18,181
- That makes me feel lonely, Clover.
- You! How do you think I feel?

616
00:55:18,231 --> 00:55:20,997
You go away and leave me with
a mother<i> I don't even know.

617
00:55:21,855 --> 00:55:24,170
I thought you and Sara Kate
were getting along better.

618
00:55:24,220 --> 00:55:26,505
- We had a talk.
<i>- About what?

619
00:55:26,555 --> 00:55:29,152
Woman stuff, Gaten,
you wouldn't understand.

620
00:55:29,940 --> 00:55:33,907
<i>But now...</i>
you can't trust her.

621
00:55:40,088 --> 00:55:42,135
Sweetheart, maybe you
shouldn't be playing up there.

622
00:55:42,285 --> 00:55:43,953
Don't tell me what to do!

623
00:55:44,003 --> 00:55:46,933
"Don't do this" and "Don't do that",
"What would Gaten say?"

624
00:55:46,983 --> 00:55:50,492
You boss me around more now than
you ever did when you were alive.

625
00:55:50,542 --> 00:55:53,215
- Clover, get down from there.
- No! I'm not listening to you!

626
00:55:53,465 --> 00:55:56,168
You're dead,
<i> I don't need you anymore!

627
00:55:56,218 --> 00:55:59,102
<i>See! You wanted me to have a new
mother,</i> and now I've got one.

628
00:55:59,152 --> 00:56:02,461
And she' gonna go away with my new
father and they're gonna take me with them.

629
00:56:02,511 --> 00:56:05,255
So, go away, I don't
need you anymore, Gaten!

630
00:56:05,505 --> 00:56:07,425
- Clover.
- Leave me alone.

631
00:56:12,018 --> 00:56:14,550
- Daddy!
<i>- Clover!

632
00:56:14,600 --> 00:56:17,697
- Daddy!
<i>- Clover!

633
00:56:18,239 --> 00:56:19,276
<i>Oh, no.

634
00:56:20,363 --> 00:56:21,286
It's all right.

635
00:56:22,036 --> 00:56:23,604
- It's all right.
- Put me down!

636
00:56:23,654 --> 00:56:25,560
Put me down!
Put me down!

637
00:56:25,610 --> 00:56:27,676
- Honey, c'mon.
- Leave me alone!

638
00:56:41,833 --> 00:56:43,316
Good night, Clover.

639
00:56:57,455 --> 00:56:59,329
Please close my door.

640
00:57:00,553 --> 00:57:02,630
I don't want you spying on me.

641
00:57:42,079 --> 00:57:43,626
Gaten?

642
00:57:45,571 --> 00:57:46,795
I'm here.

643
00:57:53,641 --> 00:57:55,250
Clover told me you're goin' away.

644
00:57:56,341 --> 00:57:58,522
- And she meant it.
- No, no, no.

645
00:57:58,851 --> 00:58:01,127
Whatever she said to
you, she didn't mean it.

646
00:58:04,494 --> 00:58:07,244
Even if she did,
she still needs you.

647
00:58:10,960 --> 00:58:12,216
What about you?

648
00:58:15,012 --> 00:58:16,949
Do you need me?

649
00:58:17,324 --> 00:58:19,006
No, no I can't.

650
00:58:21,347 --> 00:58:24,192
I can't, somebody has to
stay sane around here.

651
00:58:37,340 --> 00:58:38,469
Gaten.

652
00:59:35,733 --> 00:59:37,234
How was the gifted
and talented class?

653
00:59:37,284 --> 00:59:40,469
I'm not going back
to that school... ever.

654
00:59:48,911 --> 00:59:51,658
It's your turn,
Gaten, yeah, yeah.

655
00:59:55,212 --> 00:59:57,998
Ha! I won again.
Hit restart.

656
01:00:02,243 --> 01:00:04,621
<i>Three in a row,
I win, Gaten.

657
01:00:06,466 --> 01:00:12,552
Why did you go there? Ah, man!
<i>You start this time. You're X.

658
01:00:16,223 --> 01:00:18,208
- Clover.
