659
01:00:18,549 --> 01:00:20,142
Eh, it was a game.

660
01:00:20,878 --> 01:00:23,357
See, when Gaten was busy on the computer,

661
01:00:23,407 --> 01:00:25,436
he'd tell her, "You play for me."

662
01:00:25,486 --> 01:00:29,437
And she'd play and when she
was finished she'd say,

663
01:00:29,487 --> 01:00:32,017
- "You lose again, Gaten."
- Gaten.

664
01:00:33,761 --> 01:00:37,620
<i>Oh, yes!</i> All she needs
is an abundance of love.

665
01:00:37,670 --> 01:00:39,291
That's what Aunt Katie said.

666
01:00:40,469 --> 01:00:43,747
Now, if you don't mind,
Sara Kate...

667
01:00:43,897 --> 01:00:46,712
I'd like t' get to what we
asked you over to talk about.

668
01:00:46,762 --> 01:00:49,965
Oh? I thought it was Clover.

669
01:00:51,493 --> 01:00:55,058
Sara Kate,
money will never be a problem,

670
01:00:55,108 --> 01:00:57,807
but since Gaten
didn't leave a will,

671
01:01:00,640 --> 01:01:01,848
Yes.

672
01:01:02,253 --> 01:01:07,118
We thought it might be a
good idea if you made a will.

673
01:01:07,168 --> 01:01:08,685
- Soon.
- Soon.

674
01:01:10,031 --> 01:01:11,718
What's the rush?

675
01:01:14,137 --> 01:01:15,748
You're frightening me,
what is it?

676
01:01:16,425 --> 01:01:20,700
Well, Chase Porter was at
your house the other day.

677
01:01:20,750 --> 01:01:22,449
Yes, he was.

678
01:01:22,499 --> 01:01:24,773
Has he been coming to
your house for dinner?

679
01:01:25,479 --> 01:01:27,043
Yes, but...

680
01:01:27,093 --> 01:01:29,237
<i>- what does that have to do...</i>
- See, Sara Kate,

681
01:01:29,287 --> 01:01:32,441
this land has been in the family
for over a hundred years.

682
01:01:32,491 --> 01:01:36,188
In fact, it's the oldest black
owned piece of land in the county.

683
01:01:36,821 --> 01:01:39,465
We want to make sure
it stays in the family.

684
01:01:40,748 --> 01:01:44,249
And you think Chase Porter and
I are going to take your land?

685
01:01:50,752 --> 01:01:53,952
Someone needs a psychiatrist
and it's not Clover.

686
01:01:54,502 --> 01:01:57,397
Sara Kate, I'm sorry if I
made your feel uncomfortable.

687
01:01:57,447 --> 01:02:01,288
<i>Uncomfortable?</i> This is the most
at home I've felt since I got here.

688
01:02:01,338 --> 01:02:04,423
<i>You... you are exactly
like my family back home.

689
01:02:04,473 --> 01:02:07,437
<i>My father and my brothers are</i> in real
estate, they think JUST like you.

690
01:02:07,487 --> 01:02:09,914
I mean, of course, with them it's,
"Watch out for the blacks".

691
01:02:09,964 --> 01:02:12,431
<i>And with you it's,
"Watch out for the whites".

692
01:02:12,481 --> 01:02:14,429
But other than that,
Aunt Katie was right,

693
01:02:14,479 --> 01:02:17,054
it's not about race,
it's just family.

694
01:02:19,442 --> 01:02:21,087
Thanks for a lovely dinner.

695
01:02:22,935 --> 01:02:24,272
What about the will?

696
01:02:25,080 --> 01:02:27,373
I'm afraid you're just gonna
have to trust me on that.

697
01:02:27,423 --> 01:02:30,474
I'm only trying to protect
my husband's land.

698
01:02:30,724 --> 01:02:32,922
Is she speaking for you,
Jim Ed?

699
01:02:33,208 --> 01:02:36,803
Boud Ellis' house sits on
property that used to belong to us.

700
01:02:37,156 --> 01:02:40,099
Papa sold that land to
pay for Gates tuition.

701
01:02:40,363 --> 01:02:44,129
I've lost a lot for Gaten,
<i>I don't want to lose anymore.

702
01:02:44,179 --> 01:02:46,323
I married Gaten Hill
because I loved him.

703
01:02:47,583 --> 01:02:49,728
I loved him since the moment
I met him in college.

704
01:02:51,022 --> 01:02:52,485
<i>He wrecked my life once
because he thought race

705
01:02:52,599 --> 01:02:54,577
<i>was so important he couldn't
marry a white woman.

706
01:02:54,727 --> 01:02:57,346
<i>Among other things, he didn't
think his family would approve.

707
01:02:57,396 --> 01:02:58,687
<i>So he married Brenda.

708
01:02:58,737 --> 01:03:02,635
<i>And when she died,
</i> I did not call him, HE called ME.

709
01:03:03,894 --> 01:03:08,553
