01:03:19,864 --> 01:03:22,585
It's because he is the only one
who ever came to visit me.

714
01:03:23,748 --> 01:03:24,898
Good night.

715
01:03:29,326 --> 01:03:32,697
<i>- Your family hates me.
- No, they don't.

716
01:03:34,561 --> 01:03:37,462
<i>Do they know we were on the same side
in the Civil War, that I'm from the North.

717
01:03:37,512 --> 01:03:40,540
<i>- Well, Aunt Katie likes you.
- Oh, she's so lovely.

718
01:03:41,348 --> 01:03:42,488
<i>She's okay.

719
01:03:42,538 --> 01:03:45,399
<i>She's also so blind, she probably
doesn't even know you're white.

720
01:03:47,168 --> 01:03:48,589
Gaten!

721
01:03:50,657 --> 01:03:55,610
Oh, Gaten,
not while I'm driving.

722
01:04:08,747 --> 01:04:12,070
Excuse me, I'm looking
for Sara Kate Johnston.

723
01:04:12,120 --> 01:04:13,702
Gaten...

724
01:04:14,847 --> 01:04:16,875
is this what Clover's
going through?

725
01:04:17,865 --> 01:04:21,503
Because it's hard, Gaten.
It's hard.

726
01:04:34,332 --> 01:04:36,317
But if she can do it,
so can I.

727
01:04:37,828 --> 01:04:39,035
Okay.

728
01:04:40,406 --> 01:04:41,999
I'm lookin' for Sara Kate.

729
01:04:42,349 --> 01:04:44,493
I'm Sara Kate Johnston.

730
01:04:44,668 --> 01:04:47,254
And I'm Gaten Hill,
your math tutor.

731
01:04:47,304 --> 01:04:49,800
- But you're...
- Black.

732
01:04:52,587 --> 01:04:56,547
- Is there going to be a problem?
- No. No.

733
01:04:56,597 --> 01:04:59,521
I was going to say, "You're handsome",
and yeah...

734
01:04:59,986 --> 01:05:01,715
that could be a problem.

735
01:05:04,344 --> 01:05:05,674
Gaten.

736
01:05:07,735 --> 01:05:08,809
Gaten.

737
01:05:13,447 --> 01:05:14,761
Gaten.

738
01:05:29,585 --> 01:05:35,043
Ya know, I always hoped I'd
marry somebody just like you.

739
01:05:36,709 --> 01:05:38,176
I always thought
you'd be black.

740
01:05:38,226 --> 01:05:42,825
Oh, Gaten, I don't want
to remember this part.

741
01:05:43,559 --> 01:05:48,458
Yeah, well, we gotta talk
about it sometime, Sara Kate.

742
01:05:49,293 --> 01:05:50,556
Well...

743
01:05:52,296 --> 01:05:55,570
I always thought I'd marry
somebody just like you, only...

744
01:05:59,835 --> 01:06:02,010
it doesn't make any difference,
does it?

745
01:06:03,206 --> 01:06:04,837
We love each other.

746
01:06:08,059 --> 01:06:08,984
No!

747
01:06:09,294 --> 01:06:10,450
No!

748
01:06:12,050 --> 01:06:13,945
This almost killed
me the first time.

749
01:06:14,995 --> 01:06:18,452
Enough!
Enough!

750
01:06:44,610 --> 01:06:46,235
Come on, Katie, pick up.

751
01:06:47,527 --> 01:06:49,000
Sara Kate.

752
01:06:49,938 --> 01:06:53,765
I know it's been a... long time.

753
01:06:53,815 --> 01:06:55,049
Do you even remember me.

754
01:06:55,099 --> 01:06:56,831
Please don't.

755
01:06:57,916 --> 01:07:00,587
My wife died a while back, Sara Kate, and...

756
01:07:01,153 --> 01:07:03,417
I just need
somebody to talk to.

757
01:07:05,269 --> 01:07:07,147
I had no one else to call.

758
01:07:10,182 --> 01:07:13,250
I know there's no good reason
you should see me, but...

759
01:07:13,990 --> 01:07:17,241
- can you and me talk?
- I should've said no.

760
01:07:17,291 --> 01:07:18,496
Please?

761
01:07:19,702 --> 01:07:23,143
I see.
This weekend?

762
01:07:23,671 --> 01:07:25,090
I'll be there.

763
01:07:26,909 --> 01:07:30,416
Let's stop there,
Gaten, please.

764
01:07:30,907 --> 01:07:32,805
<i>- Hello</i>
- Katie?

765
01:07:34,705 --> 01:07:38,397
Aunt Katie, I know it's late, but...

766
01:07:39,926 --> 01:07:43,335
I'll come to get you...you
just stay the night here.

767
01:07:44,125 --> 01:07:45,926
<i>I'll be on the porch waiting.

768
01:07:51,754 --> 01:07:52,917
No!

769
01:07:54,226 --> 01:07:57,265
<i>I want you to promise me
you'll look after Clover.

770
01:07:57,415 --> 01:07:58,647
<i>No matter what.

771
01:07:59,713 --> 01:08:02,930
<i>I can barely get myself through the day,
how am I going to look after her?

772
01:08:03,205 --> 01:08:05,928
<i>- She needs you.
- Huh!

773
01:08:05,978 --> 01:08:08,482
<i>She's the most self-sufficient
kid I've ever seen.

774
01:08:09,107 --> 01:08:10,285
<i>Besides...

775
01:08:11,205 --> 01:08:13,321
<i>she's got a perfect father.

776
01:08:13,371 --> 01:08:14,614
Exactly!

777
01:08:15,355 --> 01:08:17,651
I've always had to be
perfect to get where I am.

778
01:08:18,041 --> 01:08:22,034
And Clover's worked hard to be a
perfect daughter to please me.

779
01:08:22,416 --> 01:08:25,851
God, I envy you both.

780
01:08:26,804 --> 01:08:30,176
Don't, a perfect world is fragile.

781
01:08:30,626 --> 01:08:34,003
And when her world falls apart,
she'll need you, not a perfect father.

782
01:08:34,619 --> 01:08:37,443
Why, because I know the territory?

783
01:08:37,493 --> 01:08:39,933
Thanks for throwing that in
my face on our wedding night.

784
01:08:39,983 --> 01:08:43,190
- Come on, it's your strength.
- I'm not strong.

785
01:08:44,737 --> 01:08:47,657
You always confuse strong and
tough... they're different.

786
01:08:47,707 --> 01:08:51,856
Okay... I'll be there
to pick up the pieces.

787
01:08:53,379 --> 01:08:55,429
- Good.
- Okay.

788
01:08:56,633 --> 01:09:00,597
No, no, I want you to keep me
from picking up the pieces.

789
01:09:00,848 --> 01:09:02,742
Let that perfect world shatter.

790
01:09:03,439 --> 01:09:05,790
How else will Clover ever
find out what kind of young

791
01:09:05,840 --> 01:09:08,639
woman is living inside of
that perfect little girl?

792
01:09:14,382 --> 01:09:20,148
I promise to protect her from
you... and your perfect ways,

793
01:09:22,317 --> 01:09:24,545
to love her with all my heart.

794
01:09:24,695 --> 01:09:26,009
Hold on to her.

795
01:09:26,459 --> 01:09:28,294
I will, always.

796
01:09:29,261 --> 01:09:31,543
It's like I'm holding you.

797
01:09:40,285 --> 01:09:45,083
I can't deal with it,
can't do it.

798
01:09:45,133 --> 01:09:49,233
- I can't do it, I can't do it.
- Sara Kate

799
01:09:49,283 --> 01:09:53,138
I can't do it.

800
01:09:53,188 --> 01:09:56,300
You've done it,
you've already done it.

801
01:09:57,563 --> 01:10:00,486
It's all right, it's all right,
it's okay, it's okay.

802
01:10:15,812 --> 01:10:18,605
<i>Sara Kate and Everleen are gonna
find out, you know that, don't you?

803
01:10:18,666 --> 01:10:20,835
How, they never talk to each other.

804
01:10:53,174 --> 01:10:54,840
What do you think you're doing?

805
01:10:56,091 --> 01:10:58,380
I'm doing what Gaten
should've done a long time ago...

806
01:10:58,430 --> 01:11:01,450
fixing this house, and then...

807
01:11:01,812 --> 01:11:03,587
we're going to Chase's
daughter's birthday party.

808
01:11:03,637 --> 01:11:06,301
I have to work,
most definitely.

809
01:11:14,281 --> 01:11:17,819
Perfect Chase's daughter's birthday party.

810
01:11:37,031 --> 01:11:38,492
You're both out
of the game.

811
01:11:38,542 --> 01:11:40,412
What're you talkin' about?

812
01:11:40,662 --> 01:11:42,707
I haven't had such a good
time in I don't know when.

813
01:11:43,439 --> 01:11:44,875
Shame Clover couldn't come.

814
01:11:44,925 --> 01:11:48,168
Yeah, her aunt keeps
her awfully busy working.

815
01:11:50,698 --> 01:11:52,096
Besides...

816
01:11:53,112 --> 01:11:54,690
I'm not sure your family
would have been too happy

817
01:11:54,740 --> 01:11:57,280
to see you entertaining a
woman with a black daughter.

818
01:11:57,430 --> 01:11:59,852
This isn't the old days, Sara Kate.

819
01:11:59,902 --> 01:12:01,015
Think you sister
knows that.

820
01:12:01,062 --> 01:12:03,268
Aw, hell, can't go by Mary Ellen.

821
01:12:03,753 --> 01:12:07,470
Mary Ellen thinks she pretty uppity-crusty
now that she married herself some money.

822
01:12:08,163 --> 01:12:11,152
A year ago just to pay the rent, she
worked as hard as a damned nigger woman.

823
01:12:11,302 --> 01:12:12,366
WHAT?

824
01:12:17,030 --> 01:12:20,226
- I'm sorry.
- Not the old day, huh?

825
01:12:24,258 --> 01:12:25,302
Wait, don't go away, please.

826
01:12:25,333 --> 01:12:27,876
- I've gotta get...
- No, no, stay.

827
01:12:27,926 --> 01:12:32,309
- Let go of me!
- Please, please, don't let me interrupt.

828
01:12:32,812 --> 01:12:36,314
I just came by to drop off a present
to one of my favorite students.

829
01:12:36,594 --> 01:12:38,424
Well, Claire'll be happy t' see ya.

830
01:12:38,474 --> 01:12:39,793
Yes...

831
01:12:40,022 --> 01:12:43,840
I certainly am happy to see
you're feeling better, Mrs. Hill.

832
01:12:43,890 --> 01:12:47,769
I take it the... uh...
cancer is in remission.

833
01:12:47,819 --> 01:12:49,900
Cancer?
I feel fine.

834
01:12:50,549 --> 01:12:52,737
Oh... well...

835
01:12:52,968 --> 01:12:56,986
then you might want to let Clover
come to school every once in a while.

836
01:12:57,036 --> 01:13:00,300
What are you talking about? I take her
to school myself, every morning.

837
01:13:00,350 --> 01:13:01,381
Really?

838
01:13:02,768 --> 01:13:06,603
Well, did... did you know she hasn't
been in school for the past two weeks.

839
01:13:27,135 --> 01:13:30,068
Okay, Everleen,
I've put up with a lot from you!

840
01:13:30,218 --> 01:13:33,318
I've put up with your
coldness, your rudeness,

841
01:13:33,368 --> 01:13:36,104
- your suspicion, your voodoo...
- Voodoo?

842
01:13:36,154 --> 01:13:38,457
But when it comes to Clover,
you've gone too far!

843
01:13:38,507 --> 01:13:40,077
I've gone too far?

844
01:13:40,127 --> 01:13:42,322
You're the one come down here
actin' all high and mighty

845
01:13:42,372 --> 01:13:45,298
tryin' to buy the child's
affection with bicycles.

846
01:13:45,348 --> 01:13:47,681
Bicycle!
One bicycle!

847
01:13:47,731 --> 01:13:50,035
- Damn it!
- Don't you cuss at me.

848
01:13:50,085 --> 01:13:51,879
Don't you go accusing me of
trying to steal your land.

849
01:13:51,929 --> 01:13:54,183
I have worked this peach
orchard day and night.

850
01:13:54,233 --> 01:13:56,135
I offered to help,
but you wouldn't let me.

851
01:13:56,211 --> 01:13:59,518
Well, how would you have time, you're so
busy tryin' to steal that child away.

852
01:13:59,568 --> 01:14:01,605
When she ran away from
your house, she ran to me.

853
01:14:01,655 --> 01:14:04,806
Of course she did, with you buyin'
her buying bicycles, all the time.

854
01:14:04,856 --> 01:14:09,004
A bicycle! One bicycle! She's a kid,
she's supposed to play once in a while.

855
01:14:09,054 --> 01:14:12,196
You have her down here working all day long
and I don't even get a chance to see her.

856
01:14:12,246 --> 01:14:15,322
Me? You're the one that has the
child locked up in the house.

857
01:14:15,372 --> 01:14:16,752
I can put up with all of that...

858
01:14:17,355 --> 01:14:20,601
but lying, so you can keep her out
of school to work for you here.

859
01:14:20,651 --> 01:14:23,089
- I mean, really, that is low!
- Wait a minute!

860
01:14:23,139 --> 01:14:25,339
- Wait a minute!
- And WRONG!

861
01:14:25,389 --> 01:14:27,988
And if you needed a worker,
I offered to help you!

862
01:14:28,038 --> 01:14:30,940
Now! Wait a minute!
What are you talkin' about?

863
01:14:30,990 --> 01:14:33,579
I'm talking about the letters
you're writing to school,

864
01:14:33,629 --> 01:14:36,633
saying that Clover has to stay
home to take care of her sick mother

865
01:14:36,683 --> 01:14:38,950
I didn't write any letters.

866
01:14:41,944 --> 01:14:43,850
You haven't written any letters

867
01:14:43,949 --> 01:14:46,661
saying that Clover has to stay
home because I have cancer?

868
01:14:46,711 --> 01:14:48,735
Will you listen to yourself?

869
01:14:52,559 --> 01:14:54,751
She hasn't been down
here working with you?

870
01:14:54,801 --> 01:14:56,686
- I thought she was with you.
- I thought she was with you.

871
01:15:02,688 --> 01:15:07,400
Oh!!!
We have been had!

872
01:15:08,488 --> 01:15:11,003
- Sorry.
- Well, you should be.

873
01:15:11,053 --> 01:15:15,053
How could you believe that I would do
anything to keep that child out of school?

874
01:15:15,103 --> 01:15:17,798
Well, it doesn't help with you
practicing that voodoo against me.

875
01:15:17,848 --> 01:15:19,295
I beg your pardon!

876
01:15:19,348 --> 01:15:22,511
Just because I'm a black woman,
does not mean I am practicing voodoo.

877
01:15:22,561 --> 01:15:25,161
Now, I am a god-fearing,
church-going woman.

878
01:15:25,211 --> 01:15:28,889
- I know, I know.
- Where did you get an idea like that?

879
01:15:29,974 --> 01:15:33,675
- Clover said you threw the bones.
<i>- And you believed her?

880
01:15:34,314 --> 01:15:36,425
You know, you're lettin' that
child get totally out of control.

881
01:15:36,507 --> 01:15:38,606
She comes out the house
dressed in God knows what.

882
01:15:38,635 --> 01:15:40,033
You think I let her
go out that way?

883
01:15:40,083 --> 01:15:41,501
Well, that's what she said.

884
01:15:42,080 --> 01:15:43,564
And you believed her?

885
01:15:43,614 --> 01:15:46,511
Excuse me,
is this painting for sale?

886
01:15:49,729 --> 01:15:50,988
It certainly is.

887
01:15:51,038 --> 01:15:53,000
I just made an offer of
fifty dollars for it.

888
01:15:53,575 --> 01:15:55,085
Well, I'm prepared to better that offer.

889
01:15:55,135 --> 01:15:58,253
Seventy-five, if the artist
is an authentic primitive.

890
01:15:58,562 --> 01:16:03,361
- I beg your pardon?
- He wants to know if the painter's black.

891
01:16:04,322 --> 01:16:06,435
Primitive paintings are getting
valuable again, I guess.

892
01:16:06,485 --> 01:16:10,845
Well, I don't know if the painter
is an authentic primitive,

893
01:16:10,895 --> 01:16:12,964
but I can tell you this...

894
01:16:13,464 --> 01:16:16,005
it was painted by a
member of my family.

895
01:16:16,495 --> 01:16:18,141
Great, I'll take it

896
01:16:18,191 --> 01:16:20,135
There's eighty.

897
01:16:21,572 --> 01:16:23,088
Wow! It's still wet.

898
01:16:23,532 --> 01:16:28,648
Yeah, like the sign says, we've got
the freshest peaches in the county.

899
01:16:28,803 --> 01:16:30,911
- Thank you.
- Uh-huh.

900
01:16:33,177 --> 01:16:35,407
- White people.
- Now, what am I supposed to do with this?

901
01:16:35,457 --> 01:16:37,025
Haven't you ever
sold a peach before?

902
01:16:37,075 --> 01:16:40,794
Not for seventy-five dollars.
How fast can you paint peaches?

903
01:16:42,613 --> 01:16:44,352
What are we gonna
do about that girl?

904
01:16:46,012 --> 01:16:49,821
- Can you come to dinner tonight?
- Clover says you're a terrible cook.

905
01:16:53,832 --> 01:16:55,318
And you believe her?

906
01:16:58,557 --> 01:17:00,529
Are you invitin' Chase Porter?

907
01:17:03,454 --> 01:17:05,209
Now, Everleen,
you know better than that...

908
01:17:05,652 --> 01:17:07,844
this is going to
be a family dinner.

909
01:17:11,615 --> 01:17:13,124
Okay.

910
01:17:17,696 --> 01:17:19,629
Are you sure they won't
know you did the cooking?

911
01:17:19,879 --> 01:17:24,627
I'm withholding some of the
ingredients, they'll think it was you.

912
01:17:25,519 --> 01:17:27,027
Auntie Katie.

913
01:17:32,126 --> 01:17:35,474
- Hi, Clover.
- We've been waiting grace for you.

914
01:17:37,220 --> 01:17:38,780
What are you all doing here?

915
01:17:39,936 --> 01:17:43,674
Can't we have a quiet, family
meal without havin' to explain it?

916
01:17:43,724 --> 01:17:44,708
No!

917
01:17:49,290 --> 01:17:50,901
Please say grace, Jim Ed.

918
01:17:56,183 --> 01:18:01,298
Heavenly Father, we<i> want to thank you once
again for the bounty you've given our family,

919
01:18:01,888 --> 01:18:04,771
<i>and allowing us to share it
</i>together under this roof,

920
01:18:04,821 --> 01:18:08,152
and we thank you for the
love of our departed brother,

921
01:18:08,202 --> 01:18:12,257
husband, and dear friend,
whose spirit resides here with us.

922
01:18:12,307 --> 01:18:15,930
<i>We say these things
in Jesus' name. Amen.

923
01:18:17,976 --> 01:18:20,770
- Who cooked this?
- I did.

924
01:18:21,293 --> 01:18:24,599
- No you didn't.
<i>- Where are your manners, Clover?

925
01:18:25,122 --> 01:18:27,320
This is a beautiful meal, Sara Kate.

926
01:18:28,472 --> 01:18:31,918
There are a lot of cookbooks out
there, if you can read, you can cook.

927
01:18:33,573 --> 01:18:38,480
Have you been reading anything
interesting in school these days, Clover?

928
01:18:38,959 --> 01:18:41,227
You know, just the usual.

929
01:18:41,277 --> 01:18:42,834
Pass the potatoes.

930
01:18:43,054 --> 01:18:44,918
You've been doing a nice job
with the house, Sara Kate.

931
01:18:44,968 --> 01:18:48,009
- Thank you, Gideon.
- What have you been reading in school, Clover?

932
01:18:49,105 --> 01:18:50,379
Just dumb stuff.

933
01:18:50,429 --> 01:18:53,223
And if you need any help with the rain
gutters, you know I can always help out.

934
01:18:53,273 --> 01:18:55,292
<i>I haven't seen much of you
at the peach shed, Clover,

935
01:18:55,318 --> 01:18:57,677
what've you been doing
with yourself after school?

936
01:18:57,727 --> 01:19:01,080
Miss Kenny keeps me a lot...
after school.

937
01:19:01,130 --> 01:19:02,348
<i>- Well, that's interesting news.
- Pass the beans.

938
01:19:02,543 --> 01:19:06,066
<i>Because I ran into</i> Miss Kenny today and she
said she hasn't been keeping you after school.

939
01:19:06,620 --> 01:19:07,962
Oh, pass the gravy.

940
01:19:09,325 --> 01:19:11,591
She said you haven't been at
school for the past two weeks.

941
01:19:11,641 --> 01:19:12,585
Pass the peas.

942
01:19:13,301 --> 01:19:15,750
- You mean you been cuttin' school all this time?
- Let her be.

943
01:19:17,050 --> 01:19:18,813
Where have you been, Clover?
What have you been doing?

944
01:19:19,555 --> 01:19:20,690
Pass the corn.,
pass the salt.

945
01:19:20,764 --> 01:19:21,802
Now that you have all the food,

946
01:19:21,852 --> 01:19:23,127
would you care to tell
